President Trump delivered a speech at the Project Safe Neighborhoods conference in Kansas City, Missouri, where he announced the nomination of William Barr as the new Attorney General. He praised law enforcement officials and expressed his commitment to restoring respect for law enforcement. He also discussed his administration's efforts to combat crime, secure the border, and enforce immigration laws. Trump emphasized the importance of partnerships between federal, state, and local law enforcement agencies and highlighted the successes of these collaborations in reducing violent crime. He called for Congress to fully fund border security and praised the work of ICE officers in arresting criminal aliens. The president also discussed his administration's efforts to reform the prison system and help former inmates reintegrate into society. Overall, Trump reiterated his commitment to making America safe and praised the men and women in law enforcement for their dedication and service.